				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} T_\mathrm{n}(x(t))= 2 \pi \sqrt{\frac{M+A(x(t))}{G(x(t))}}. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}Consequently, the instantaneous damped natural period depends on the instantaneous natural period as well as on the hydrodynamics of the system.13TL(x(t))=Tn(x(t))f(B,M,A).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
