				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\zeta $$\end{document} of about 0.1, which in turn make the damped natural period rise from 0.693 to 0.698 s.

The adaptive strategy code is nested in the constant algorithm shown in Fig. 3. The constant latching duration algorithm takes care of applying the control when peaks occur, using the latching period previously established by the adaptive algorithm. As shown in Fig. 6, the adaptive strategy is coded right before the latching algorithm and eventually modifies the latching duration.Fig. 6
